  <section class="bg-gray-50 py-16"><div class="section"><div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
    <div>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">St. Paul Fire Code Requirements</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">The City of St. Paul enforces the Minnesota State Fire Code (which adopts the IFC with Minnesota amendments) through the Saint Paul Fire Department Fire Prevention Division. As Minnesota's capital city and the eastern anchor of the Twin Cities metro area, St. Paul oversees a commercial landscape spanning the Lowertown arts and entertainment district, the Capitol and government office corridor, Grand Avenue retail and restaurant strip, and significant industrial operations along the Mississippi River.</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">St. Paul's cold climate — with winter temperatures routinely below 0°F — creates fire protection system challenges similar to other northern cities. Wet pipe sprinkler systems in unheated spaces risk freezing. Heating equipment fires are a significant concern during Minnesota winters. The city's aging commercial building stock, particularly in the historic Lowertown and West 7th Street corridors, frequently requires fire system upgrades when occupancy changes occur.</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Key standards include <a href="/compliance/nfpa-10/" class="text-red-brand hover:underline">NFPA 10</a>, <a href="/compliance/nfpa-72/" class="text-red-brand hover:underline">NFPA 72</a>, and <a href="/compliance/nfpa-25/" class="text-red-brand hover:underline">NFPA 25</a>.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-200 mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-4">St. Paul Fire Prevention Contacts</h3>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
          <div><p class="text-sm font-bold text-gray-800">Saint Paul Fire Department — Fire Prevention</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-600">100 E. 11th Street, Saint Paul, MN 55101</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-600">Phone: (651) 224-7811</p></div>
          <div class="border-t border-gray-100 pt-3"><p class="text-sm font-bold text-gray-800">Minnesota State Fire Marshal Division</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-600">Licensing & Enforcement: (651) 201-7200</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
